A taxi patroller was shot multiple times at the Cavendish Mall, Kempton Park on Tuesday afternoon. Allegations are that the victim went into the mall to buy food when he was accosted by unknown men and was subsequently shot. Gauteng police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said when the victim, who was driving a taxi patrol vehicle, was about to leave the mall, a vehicle blocked him while an occupant of a white Dodge fired shot at him. “He was blocked by a black Opel Corsa, and another man from a white Dodge fired several shots at him,” Dlamini said. He added that the victim sustained gunshot wounds and was taken to hospital for treatment after sustaining multiple gunshot wounds. Dlamini added that the victim’s condition was currently unknown and that no one has been arrested yet. The motive for the shooting is also not known. Police are investigating the motive behind the attack and are appealing to anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of the attackers to contact their nearest police station or Crime Stop line on 08600 10111. The Star 